<div style="float:right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em;">[[Image:Marion County Georgia.png]]</div>

'''Marion County''' is a [[county]] located in the [[U.S. state|state]] of [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], [[USA]]. It was created on December 14, 1827. It is part of the [[Columbus, Georgia]]-[[Alabama]] [[Metropolitan Statistical Area]]. As of [[2000]], the population is 7,144.  The 2005 Census Estimate shows a population of 7,244 [http://www.census.gov/popest/counties/tables/CO-EST2005-01-13.xls].  The [[county seat]] is [[Buena Vista, Georgia]][[Geographic references|<sup>6</sup>]]. The art site of [[Pasaquan]] is located in Marion County.

==Geography==
According to the [[U.S. Census Bureau]], the county has a total area of 951 [[km<U+00B2>]] (367 [[square mile|mi<U+00B2>]]).  951 km<U+00B2> (367 mi<U+00B2>) of it is land and 1 km<U+00B2> (0.386 mi<U+00B2>) of it (0.13%) is water.{{fact}}
